  "wikitext": "\n'''2-6-030\n\nAlternative term: (Unlighted) Beacon (G.B.) Daybeacon (U.S.A.)\n\nAn unlighted navigation mark.\n\n\nNote: In the U.S.A. the word \"Daymark\" is also used for the daytime character of an aid to navigation.\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Daymark}}\n[[Category:2.6 Visual Aids in general: Buoyage and Beaconage]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 2023 Revision]]"
